.TH SH 1 "May 2024" "Version 1.0" "Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
shell \- Simple Shell

.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
\fB./shell\fR
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fB./shell\fR command calls Simple Shell, minimalistic but powerful 
command line interface designed for seamless interaction with the system.
Shell provides users with an intuitive environment to execute commands and 
manage workflow efficiently.

.SH OPTIONS
None.

.SH USAGE
To start the Simple Shell, execute the following command:
.nf
\fB$ ./shell\fR
.fi
Upon launching the shell, users will gain access to a versatile toolkit
for managing files, executing programs, and customizing their system 
environment.

.SH EXAMPLES
Below are some illustrative examples that shows the functionality of 
the Simple Shell:
.nf
\fB$ ./shell
#cisfun$ ls
Desktop  Documents  Downloads  Music  Pictures  Videos

#cisfun$ echo "Hello, World!"
Hello, World!

#cisfun$ env
PATH=/usr/local/bin:/usr/bin:/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/sbin:/sbin
SHELL=/bin/bash
HOME=/home/user
...

#cisfun$ exit
.fi

.SH SEE ALSO
bash(1), zsh(1), csh(1)

